A weathered stone statue of Lady Justice standing in a grand courthouse hall, her scales dramatically unbalanced with one side touching the ground, her blindfold slipping off to reveal one eye, rendered in a vintage sepia-toned photographic style reminiscent of 1940s documentary photography, dramatic shadows cast through tall arched windows creating bars of light across the marble floor, dust motes floating in the air, the statue showing signs of age with small cracks and moss growing at its base, atmospheric and melancholic mood suggesting institutional decay.
